  <item>
    <title>Heart of Darkness</title>
    <link>http://quietlittlelies.com/exercise/heart-darkness</link>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;Take me upriver, to Kurtz:&lt;br /&gt;
I’ll find him, and help him, without fail.&lt;br /&gt;
We make our way past severed heads; then, look: it’s him!&lt;br /&gt;
On a stretcher, deathly pale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can’t leave him behind:&lt;br /&gt;
Though he’s found, he’s lost his mind;&lt;br /&gt;
If you stray beyond the ambit of sense,&lt;br /&gt;
Horror! is all you will find.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
     <category domain="http://quietlittlelies.com/category/exercise-type/literary-classic">Literary classic</category>
 <pubDate>Sun, 29 May 2011 16:34:09 +0000</pubDate>
