  <item>
    <title>Ulysses</title>
    <link>http://quietlittlelies.com/exercise/ulysses</link>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;Stephen and Leopold wake,&lt;br /&gt;
Then set off round Dublin, both on foot.&lt;br /&gt;
All day they wander, meet, then wander off again,&lt;br /&gt;
Till the young man gets half-cut.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Nighttown, in distress,&lt;br /&gt;
Stephen’s helped by Bloom, no less;&lt;br /&gt;
Still, they’re home in time for Molly to dream:&lt;br /&gt;
“yes I said yes I will Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
     <category domain="http://quietlittlelies.com/category/exercise-type/literary-classic">Literary classic</category>
